 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               9455 1451
                                                                  9455 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                9455 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               9455 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             9455 1451
                                                                  9455 1451
 This code integrates into a single system a number               9455 1451
 of important modules and features:                               9455 1451
                                                                  9455 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 9455 1451
   coupled-channels code ECIS06 by J. Raynal                      9455 1451
 - Soft-rotator deformed Optical Model including                  9455 1451
   coupled-channels code OPTMAN by E.Soukhovitskii                9455 1451
   and coworkers                                                  9455 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    9455 1451
   width fluctuation correction, and the                          9455 1451
   optical model for fission with partial damping                 9455 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                9455 1451
   TRISTAN by H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                       9455 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      9455 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 9455 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                9455 1451
 - Hybrid Monte Carlo preequilibrium model(M.Blann)               9455 1451
   (code DDHMS by M.Chadwick, mod. by B.V.Carlson)                9455 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   9455 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                9455 1451
   discrete transitions                                           9455 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [RIPL]                9455 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                9455 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               9455 1451
   and gamma strength functions based on the RIPL                 9455 1451
   library [RIPL]                                                 9455 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              9455 1451
   EXFOR library                                                  9455 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A.Trkov)                     9455 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 9455 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                9455 1451
   PrePro codes by D. Cullen                                      9455 1451
 - ENDF checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                   9455 1451
 - Highly automated fitting of optical model                      9455 1451
   parameters (by B.V. Carlson)                                   9455 1451
 - KALMAN code for fitting experimental data and                  9455 1451
 - generating covariances                                         9455 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               9455 1451
